A unique "electronic goods ticket" for return goods Setouchi City added with hometown tax: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San Diego
"The City Gift."
it's settled by contacting a dedicated device.
Setouchi City announced on the 27th that it would add its own electronic goods ticket "e-machi Gift" to the home tax return.
It is available at member stores in the city from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay the hometown tax and choose an electronic ticket as a reward item, 30% of the donation amount will be sent to the designated smartphone.
When a product is purchased, it shows the screen of the product ticket, and the shop side pays by contacting the stamp-type dedicated equipment.
They cannot be sold or sold.
Recipients usually require a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but can receive an electronic ticket instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five Hometown Tax Portals, there are also two special sites in the city.
Currently, there are 13 member stores, aiming to reach 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications (MIC) established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition among local governments.
The city has stated that "the city plans to set up merchants who handle local products as members and within the guidelines."
In the 18th year of Setouchi City, the hometown tax amount is about 430 million yen.
