Driving in high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving the wrong pedal of young people - Yahoo! News
Violations against road traffic laws
The number of reports on accidents caused by incorrect operation such as pedal treading is increasing, and it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, the number of accidents involving pedal treading errors by age (more than 1080 cases under 24 years old) exceeded 1032 cases over 75 years old.
It is important to call attention to young people as well.
you want to take your feet off?
is it safe?
There is no description of the gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike elderly people who are often thought to come from a decline in their bodies, such as driving skills and reflexes, young people may be inadvertently misled by other things such as music and conversation, or trampled errors due to clothes etc.
In particular, women choose various shoes depending on the clothes of the day, such as high heels, pumps, sandals and mules, and some people drive as they are.
Although some people know that it is not suitable for driving, it is troublesome to change clothes, some people do not think about the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people drive without evil.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates the Road Traffic Law.
The first is "Consistent operation of steering wheel, brakes and other operations" Article 70 "Consistent violation of safety driving obligation" which stipulates that "Do not drive to cause accidents and harm to people."
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that drivers must comply with the matters stipulated by each prefectural public safety committee, for example, in Article 12 of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law Enforcement Regulations, "Do not drive vehicles (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents driving operations, or by wearing shoes that may interfere with driving operations, such as slippers, hanging, high heels."
Even if it is not specified as a high heel, the purpose of each prefecture is the same as to consider driving as a violation of " footwear that may interfere with driving operation."
Why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe pedal operation, first fix the heel of the foot on the floor, place the foot to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the foot to the right as a starting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to keep firmly fixed so that the heel does not break.
However, in high heels, the area where the heel is grounded on the floor is small, and the heel always blurs out, and because the height of the heel has an angle throughout the foot, the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal becomes smaller and it is difficult to make fine adjustments that can not be firmly trampled.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material can easily catch a high-heeled heel, and pedals cannot be stepped on when suddenly braking, or high-heel can be removed from the time signature when the heel is pulled, and it can be stuck in the back of the pedal.
In addition, there are cases where the heel pulls to the back of the pedal when stepping back after stepping on the pedal, and the accelerator pedal disappears.
Toyota and Subaru Accelerate joint development (response) with new AWD vehicles and 86/BRZ next-generation models - Yahoo!News
Toyota and Subaru agreed to a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares and become an affiliate of equity method application.
Since the partnership agreement was reached in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles, supply Toyota vehicles to Subaru, and jointly develop the FR sports car 86.
In June this year, we also agreed to develop EV-specific platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's All-wheel drive technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Toyota's shareholding in Subaru is 16.83 percent of the voting rights.
The company is a subsidiary of Toyota.
On the other hand, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares equivalent to the same amount (up to 8 billion yen) as the acquisition of Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperation through business capital alliances.
We will jointly develop AWD and 86/BRZ models, expand the installation of THS (Toyota Hybrid System) in Subaru vehicles, coordinate in the connected area, and promote technological collaboration in the autonomous driving field.
U.S., at least 18,000 refugees for three consecutive years | Shizuoka Shimbun
Washington, D.C. On October 26, the U.S. Department of State announced a policy to reduce the number of refugees accepted from around the world to 18,000 in the fiscal year 2020 (October 19-20).
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal strict immigration and refugee policies to the conservatives in the presidential election next year.
It is inevitable that criticisms from human rights groups and other organizations will be made in the midst of the constant number of people being driven out of the country in various places.
The former Obama administration set the maximum limit for fiscal 2017 to 110,000, but the Trump administration, which was inaugurated in January 2017, overturned it and reduced it to 50,000.
It has been reduced to 45,000 in FY18 and 30,000 in FY19.
