BITPoint, which leaked 3 billion yen worth of crypto assets, to resume service (Genfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, 3 billion yen worth of crypto asset exchanges such as Bitcoin leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., the operator of the company, announced on September 30 that it would resume the sending (remittance) service of crypto assets.
There seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence.
BITPoint leaked Bitcoin and Ripple this July.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume the service for sending (remittance) crypto assets at around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to dealing with customers who suffered damage and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as a management system including security.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume the service as soon as possible, while putting safety first, and strive to restore the trust of users."
In July of this year, the exchange suffered a cryptocurrency leak worth 3 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple.
In the subsequent press conference, regarding the continuation of the business, "There is a current account balance of about 3 billion yen even if the compensation is subtracted" "We aim to resume the service as soon as possible based on the priority of user protection."
This article was released on September 27, 2019.
