Self-improvement of safety measures at Famispo 35% of municipalities implemented, free of charge for child care | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Bereaved families in the childcare accident (right) holding a press conference on the results of the "Family Support Center Project" = On the afternoon of the 27th, Osaka Prefecture Agency
A private survey on the 27th revealed that 35% of the city, ward, town, and village that implements "Family Support Center Project" (Famispo), which connects parents who want to temporarily leave their children and aid members who are entrusted to them at their own homes, have independently strengthened safety measures.
Prior to the provision of free child education and childcare in October, the family members of the childcare accident complained that the country should make strict standards.
The "network to eliminate serious accidents in childcare" created by parents and experts who lost their children in a child-care accident was investigated by 921 municipalities.
274 municipalities responded.
The government requires only aid members to take emergency life training courses.
