<Saga Torrential Rainfall and Support Wheel< Specialty Noodles "Taromen" Perform at evacuation centers Management Co-op, Revitalizing Victims|Saga Shimbun News|Saga Shimbun
Children who enjoy the soul food "Taromen" in Omachi on the way home from the bath = Misato, Omachi Town General Welfare Center
On the night of the 25th, the "Omachi Taromen Steering Council" (representative of Kensuke Suzuyama) made at a restaurant serving "Taromen," a specialty noodle of Omachi-cho, performed "Taromen" at Misato, Machi General Welfare Center, which is a shelter for people affected by heavy rain.
It was a soul food that was loved since the Kishima coal mine was there, and cheered the people affected.
"The only thing we can do is make noodles and eat them."
Four restaurants on the taromen menu cooperated to make 90 meals and brought rice balls to shelter.
The ginger-flavored beef bone soup was filled with thin noodles, and the pork head (head) meat, shrimp, vegetables and other ingredients were abundant.
Not only those who stayed at evacuation centers, but also those who came to the baths provided "taste of Omachi."
A man (66) says, "I've been a fan since I was young, but I ate it for the first time in a year," and a 20-year-old and 22-year-old siblings who moved about a year ago and said, "I ate it for the first time, it's delicious, I want to go to the store this time."
Vice President Kenichiro Fujise, who finished cooking, ran up and said, "We will cooperate if we can do anything so that we can return to our daily life as soon as possible."
1 year after the earthquake in the eastern part of Iburi Province, water supply is secured even during power outage.
In response to the total power outage (blackout) caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City, where dewatering occurred.
According to the Water and Sewer Department of the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake, and "watering plugs" were installed that could produce water even if power outages occurred.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that supply water with a "passenger tank type" that can be cut off during a power outage.
The house's water supply system is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" that once feeds water into a receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "directly connected type" that directly feeds water from the city's water distribution pipe to each door.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting) - Yahoo!News
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search for and rescue the victims before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
60 people from the police, fire and hunting party participated in the training held at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village.
At the opening ceremony, Chief Tsukeda of the Goto Police Department called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training from this."
The training was conducted with the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home even at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search the mountain by calling the name of the missing man.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June to pick wild vegetables disappeared and was rescued the next day with injuries.
During the training, I found a man who had been injured and checked the cooperation between searching and rescue on a stretcher to go down the mountain.
