Sakura shrimp in the growth process PT in Shizuoka City, etc., taken 290 meters deep | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Sakura shrimp born this year, which was successfully photographed in the deep sea of Suruga Bay, is off Kamahara, Shimizu Ward, Shizuoka City (provided by the Yui Sakura shrimp project)
The Yui Sakura Ebi Project, a project of the Ocean Industry Cluster Council led by industry, academia, and government officials in Shizuoka City, succeeded in photographing sakura shrimp, which is thought to have been born during the spawning season this spring and summer, at a depth of 290 meters in Suruga Bay.
The video of the growth process is valuable, and the concerned parties want to lead to the elucidation of the ecology of sakura shrimp, which has many mysteries.
The photograph was taken near the bottom of the sea about 1 to 5 km off the coast of the Kamahara district, Shimizu Ward, the city.
A total of 300 were confirmed in 17 minutes.
In the daytime, the traditional knowledge that sakura shrimp in the deep sea form a certain group at the bottom of the sea was reaffirmed.
The adult body is about 40 mm long and the individual reflected is about 23 mm long.
The spawning period was determined by matching data from season to season of freshly caught sakura shrimp.
Detailed analysis is requested by Fujitsu Software Technologies and Shizuoka Technical College, which make up the team.
Keisuke Mizuno, Project Leader, said, "I want to capture the living figure of individuals in the growth process, including fry."
Mother Ranch reopened, Chiba Prefecture residents free of charge Damaged by Typhoon by the end of October | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Chiba-kun, a mascot character of Chiba Prefecture, welcomes visitors at a mother ranch that has reopened its business.
Mother Ranch in Futsu City, Chiba Prefecture, which had been closed from September 9 due to power outages and damage to facilities caused by Typhoon No.15, resumed operations on August 28.
In order to increase the number of people living in Chiba Prefecture, admission is free until the end of October.
Under the clear autumn weather, many people visited the park at the same time as the opening, and at the entrance gate, the mascot character of the prefecture "Chiba-kun" who ran to cheer was welcomed.
The roof was covered with blue sheets and some facilities continued to be repaired, but half of the restaurants were closed to reopen.
Kenji Mitani (34), a family member of Sagamihara City, said with a smile, "I was worried about when I would resume.I came to enjoy the event of potato digging because I thought it would lead to reconstruction."
