Meeting with the Minister of Health, Labor and Welfare and the Family of Leprosy Three Provincial Consultations to Eliminate Discrimination | Shizuoka Shimbun at es
Katsunobu Kato, Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare, announced at a press conference after the cabinet meeting on October 27 that he would meet with the families of former leprosy patients on October 2.
In addition, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare, Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology, and Ministry of Justice held discussions on the same day to resolve discrimination and prejudice against former patients and their families.
Mr. Kato said, "I would like to listen carefully to the voices of my family and make every effort to solve the problem."
In June, the Kumamoto District Court ordered the plaintiffs to pay a total of 376 million yen.
Prime Minister Abe Shinzō postponed the appeal and the decision was finalized.
The government was also working on compensation measures and human rights awareness.
