Publication of original manuscript before Akutagawa suicide | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
A manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, first published in the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) obtained the manuscript of his essay "Shoku Bungei-shiki, Too Bungei-shiki," which he published in his last years, fighting literary theory with Junichiro TANIZAKI, by 27th at the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Museum in Kita Ward, Tokyo.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that the essay was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that the manuscript was published publicly.
It is thought that he wrote it a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the memorial researcher, Takeshi Tanei, said, "I can see that Akutagawa, who was debilitating both physically and mentally, faced serious literary challenges with a tragic determination."
A total of 12 essays were published in the April 27 issue of Bungei Shunju.
